                {
                    "name": "Shadow Doubles",
                    "type": "stat_block_section",
                    "text": "to <img alt=\"Three Actions\" class=\"actiondark\" src=\"Images\\Actions\\ThreeActions.png\" style=\"height:15px; padding:0px 2px 0px 2px\"/><img alt=\"Three Actions\" class=\"actionlight\" src=\"Images\\Actions\\ThreeActions_I.png\" style=\"height:15px; padding:0px 2px 0px 2px\"/>  (<a aonid=\"92\" game-obj=\"Traits\"><u>illusion</u></a>, <a aonid=\"120\" game-obj=\"Traits\"><u>occult</u></a>, <a aonid=\"143\" game-obj=\"Traits\"><u>shadow</u></a>) <b>Frequency </b>once per day; <b>Effect </b>For each action spent to use this ability, the ankou creates one shadowy duplicate of themself anywhere within 60 feet of themself. Shadow doubles have the same statistics as an ankou, but they have the <a aonid=\"154\" game-obj=\"Traits\">summoned</a> trait, have 84 Hit Points, can't use Shadow Doubles or innate spells, and have an attack bonus of +25 for their Strikes. A shadow double that attempts a saving throw against a <a aonid=\"100\" game-obj=\"Traits\">light</a> effect can't get a result better than failure. Each double remains for 1 round, until it's reduced to 0 Hit Points, or until it moves further than 120 feet from the ankou, whichever comes first. Each round thereafter, the ankou can spend a single action that has the <a aonid=\"32\" game-obj=\"Traits\">concentrate</a> trait to extend the duration of surviving duplicates by 1 round, to a maximum duration of 1 minute. The ankou can see through the eyes of all of the shadow doubles at once. A character who <a aonid=\"84\" game-obj=\"Actions\">Seeks</a> can identify an ankou as real or a shadow double with a successful DC 39 Perception check.",
